The machine appears to be empty of its delicious, refreshing beverages.

"Eulogy Template—Soldier, friendly fire variation 016: [Name] devoted many hours to the prosperity of Super Earth. They may rest easy in the knowledge that the [bullets/shrapnel/concussive force] that took their life was Democratic in origin and fired in the service of Liberty."

It only takes ONE TRAITOR to destroy Utopia.

The Ministry of Unity.

Who can say what heinous deeds this machine was intended to carry out?
"EMERGENCY WARNING: Hostile forces incoming. Evacuate immediately. EMERGENCY WARNING: Hostile forces incoming. Evacuate immediately."

Truth: the backbone of Democracy.

Used to transport ore, modular dwellings, and dissident holding pens.

If you play one of our games, we will always access data from and/or store data on the device that you are using. This data is necessary to deliver our games, and includes:
•   Content Data: Game content data, such as video, audio, graphic, text, and game level information that is requested and downloaded for the game that you are accessing online. If you are playing an online game, this includes your online interactions as necessary to reflect those interactions on our game servers.
•   Account Data: Information required to sign you into your account for PlayStation™Network. 
•   Configuration Data: Information about the configuration of your device and the game you are playing, such as the device date, time and language settings and your in-game preference and settings. 
•   Security Data: Information necessary to detect and investigate malicious, unauthorised or fraudulent activity.
•   Legal Data: Information required by applicable law and to demonstrate compliance.
If you agree, we may collect more detailed information about how you interact with our games.
This may include when and how you use the game's user interface, which parts of the game you visit, which weapons you use, which characters you interact with and any errors that you encounter.
Game Data is usually sent to us and stored with one or more unique network, device and/or account identifiers.

Note: accidental kinetic displacement due to volatility of quantum-entanglement rounds is not covered by under Helldiver insurance.

If you play one of our games, we will always access data from and/or store data on the device that you are using. This data is necessary to deliver our games, and includes:
•   Content Data: Game content data, such as video, audio, graphic, text, and game level information that is requested and downloaded for the game that you are accessing online. If you are playing an online game, this includes your online interactions as necessary to reflect those interactions on our game servers.
•   Account Data: Information required to sign you into your account. 
•   Configuration Data: Information about the configuration of your device and the game you are playing, such as the device date, time and language settings and your in-game preference and settings. 
•   Security Data: Information necessary to detect and investigate malicious, unauthorised or fraudulent activity.
•   Legal Data: Information required by applicable law and to demonstrate compliance.
If you agree, we may collect more detailed information about how you interact with our games.
This may include when and how you use the game’s user interface, which parts of the game you visit, which weapons you use, which characters you interact with and any errors that you encounter.
Game Data is usually sent to us and stored with one or more unique network, device and/or account identifiers.

This includes use of Game Data to:
•   Provide you with our games.
•   Understand the usage and performance of the game you are playing, and to develop improvements to the game.
•   Develop new products and services.
•   Detect, investigate, and minimise malicious, unauthorised or fraudulent behaviour.
•   Audit, compliance and legal purposes (for example, making or defending claims or activities that are required to comply with a law).

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The DMB-500 is a evolution on the classic bombs of human history. The approach of not having any guidance system in the bomb has allowed for packing it with unprecedented amounts of conventional explosives, making for a very large explosion and resulting crater. While the bomb is not specifically designed to take out armoured targets, the explosion is massive enough that a close hit will kill almost anything, armoured or not. The drawback is that the Eagle pilot has to take more care when delivering the payload to make sure that the target is hit; this increases the response time of the bomb in comparison to other Eagle payloads.

The eagle is also susceptible to enemy anti-air weaponry and caution is advised when calling in strikes near enemy AA.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A continuation of the early A|GL-8 grenade launcher turret, this model packs a hefty punch and has variable fire distance. The turret fires in a high arch raining shots down from above, negating cover and other things in the way. The turret normally requires line of sight to its target to do the firing but this can be removed with some clever engineering.
An autonomous drone equipped with a laser rifle, providing 360° cover. Returns to backpack to cool down.
The ammunition feed is improved allowing shorter cooldowns between uses. Cooldown decreased by 15 seconds.
"We fear not poison, fear not death; spite our foes with every breath." From the beloved classic Hazard Pay: The Musical.
The Jump Pack can be used more often. The recharge cooldown is shorter.
Lethal toxins are stored within the projectile which shatter on impact
The Destroyer's laser cannon will sweep over the designated area, vaporising all targets within the effective radius.
The Ballistic Shield is larger and will cover a larger part how the Helldiver.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A precision artillery barrage fired from the 84mm Atlas Gatling cannon of a Helldiver Destroyer in low orbit. Handy for when you have to level smaller areas of the battlefield or take out enemy concentrations. The shells themselves are capable of destroying armoured targets, but requires a direct hit to do any significant amount of damage making it unreliable as an anti-tank option.
A humane compliance weapon with two separate magazines: one for armour-penetrating flechette rounds and one for stun rounds.
A heavily-armoured walking exosuit equipped with a rocket launcher and a heavy machine gun.
The Orbital Lasers can target a larger area. Search area have been increased from 50 to 60m.

A top-loaded shotgun prominently featured in the final episode of "Obedient Democracy Support Troopers".
Produced by Martian Armoury.
A semi-automatic ceremonial rifle equipped with a bayonet. Can be set to fire in three-shot bursts, to easily conduct the Fallen Hero's Salute.
Packed full of high performance gunpowder this round packs a serious punch as well as kick.

The A/AC-41 is a 40mm automatic cannon firing explosive anti-tank ammunition. The Turret is effective over long ranges and against armoured targets, but has limitations when it comes to the turn speed as the servos required for the heavier than normal weight of the gun are slower. It is therefore recommended to place the turret a respectable distance from the enemy and in a position that has good fields of fire.
A cluster fragmentation grenade. The shrapnel submunition allows it to inflict damage over a large area.
A high-calibre rifle with high damage and penetration.
Packed full of high performance gunpowder this round packs a serious punch as well as kick.
Improvements to the ready ammunition storage allows the ORBITAL BARRAGE to fire an additional salvo before having new ammunition brought up.
Even among the most depraved of dissidents, the mere sight of this armour is enough to inspire a change of heart.
A quality product, this armour can destroy over 300,000 kilometres of fencing with no decline in operational efficiency.
The recharge delay is 2 sec shorter both after taking damage and after the energy is depleted.
The main ingredient in Super Earth liberation.
An accurate, armour-penetrating rifle, the BR-14 Adjudicator delivers righteous judgement to medium-sized enemies, though its restrictive magazine limits its effectiveness against large groups.
Commemorating the New Stockholm treaty on prisoners of war, this cape celebrates the right of all enemy combatants to a swift and merciful execution.
A drone that defends its user by firing caustic gas at nearby enemies, blinding and slowing them temporarily. Returns to backpack to refill.
Bearers of this armour ride no equine mount, but are nonetheless borne to battle atop the trusty steed of Liberty.
Has less resistance and requires less pressure before the weapon starts firing.
Packed full of high performance gunpowder this round packs a serious punch as well as kick.
A modified Liberator fitted with a scope and firing armour-piercing rounds, to help users take down armoured targets.
With removal of the crewspace and improved automation, gives room for more ammunition, allowing for two additional salvos before rearming.
A projectile which explodes while airborne, creating a deadly rain of shrapnel. Not effective against heavy armour.
A machine gun designed for stationary use. Trades higher power for increased recoil and reduced accuracy.
Each servo-assisted limb contains 138 miniature motors, to support a natural gait and long-term spinal health.
A larger rocket pod allows for more rockets to be fired each run, increasing the chance that the target will be taken out.
A flare that illuminates the battlefield.
A replacement for a fallen comrade.
A targeted air strike unable to destroy buildings, but efficient at clearing smaller targets.
The Ballistic Shield can now manually detonate a flash charge on the front, stunning any enemies nearby.
Provides one-time, short-lived resuscitation upon death, given that the Helldiver's body is still intact.
A laser rifle, firing in short bursts. Does not need reloading, but if it overheats a new heat sink must be fitted.
Creates a <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> chance of surviving a lethal hit.
A paint job for use in arctic environments.
A submachine gun with an extremely high rate of fire, which can be operated with one hand. Ideal for multitasking.
The breathing apparatus built into this equipment helps both soldiers and colonists thrive, even when assigned to planets with atmospheres rated "suboptimal", "extreme", and "character building".

The dauntless pioneers of the Great Expansion, facing the un-Democratic unknown, adopted the Way of the Bandolier. With the gusto of their covering fire making up for their modest accuracy, they strived to be perfectly aligned in their shared values, and ready to serve when called upon by the machine gun of civic duty.
Additional rocket pods are installed to allow for  one more attack run before the Eagle has to rearm.
Command Centre of the Super Destroyer. The helm from which Helldivers deliver Freedom's mercy.
Electrostatically charged container that emits a distorting punch when it hits its target
The backpack needs less time to recharge between displacements. Cooldown is decreased from 60 to 45 seconds
The crew has been trained to fire two salvoes with 6 seconds fire time each. Retargeting between salvoes.
Shaving some material off the bomb casing allows for more explosive filler, resulting in a bigger boom.
A plasma igniter that reduces the vertical recoil and some of the horizontal recoil created when firing.
Triggers a stun explosion after the player has teleported. This gives the player time to recover from potential enemies.
A LAS-16 Sickle model with all overheating protections conveniently removed, allowing for far longer bursts of fire. Does more damage when overheated, at the cost of slightly burning the user.

A Dark Fluid-powered backpack that generates a portable micro-wormhole. This safe and well-understood technology allows the wearer to warp short distances. Warning: do not use while pack is overloaded.
The Rail Cannon can search a larger area to find an optimal target. Search radius is increased from 30m to 45m.
A representation of the thankfulness of those infinite descendants whose liberated existence we strive to ensure.
An angled vertical foregrip to improve the manoeuvrability of the weapon.

NOT IMPLEMENTED A high caliber sniper rifle capable of killing most infantry and other light targets with a single well placed shot. Even capable of disabling lighter vehicles by shooting out the engine, tires, or tracks.
In field tests, 84% of users said that the armour improved their posture and self-esteem.
A heavy one-handed blade. Slower to swing than other melee weapons, but deals more damage.
A symbol of Super Earth's Astral Promise: that every star shall one day illuminate throngs of joyous voters.

The 'JUSTICE' is a assault rifle that was created to aid Helldivers in battle when they need a higher calibre rifle. The magazine carries fewer rounds than the `LIBERATOR` assault rifle but each round is of a higher calibre, effective against medium-armoured targets.

Based upon the previous standard issue service rifle, this version is modified with a longer barrel and improved sight attachment options. Produced by Radow Weapons Technology, the rifle still finds use as a marksman rifle used in SEAF squads.
An expanded internal ammunition bay is installed making it possible for the EAGLE to engage with its cannons two more times before running out.
A plasma container with a 50% larger capacity.
Commonly replicated in stage adaptions of "Lady Liberty's Tower", in which young Diver Beatrick dons this armour to slay Oppressio, the Tyrant Rex.
The heavy machine gun can now switch between three different fire rates to conserve ammo or increase the damage output.
Although Super Citizen Miranda's true identity has been lost to time, most legal historians agree that she was once a patron of highly-efficient interrogation techniques.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The 'PEACEMAKER' is the standard issue sidearm for officers and security personnel. A small calibre pistol, what it lacks in stopping power, it makes up for in reliability.

Many consider their sidearm a trusted friend handy for emergency situations. Originally produced by MEY as a pistol for their internal security, the model had so many strengths that is was submitted for trials as the SEAFS standard issue sidearm and passed with flying colours.
This armour was designed by PFC Rodney A. Carmichael, the first Helldiver to use a stim on an ally instead of himself.
Fires powerful exploding bolts which do maximum damage upon direct impact. Gravity must be accounted for when aiming.
Improved gunpowder propels the projectile at higher velocity reducing the travel time and increasing damage.
The backpack is upgraded to hold more magazines for the drone, increasing the capacity from 4 to 8.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The 'SCYTHE' is a rifle based on experimental Super Earth developed laser technology. It fires a continuous beam capable of heating up surfaces to extreme temperatures in seconds.

The beam is focused on extreme distance but can be focused further using different prisms, allowing for greater damage if used correctly. Refocusing the beam reduces the efficiency for the non focused interval.

When donning the One True Flag, one must face the direction of Super Earth, recite the Super Earth Anthem, and salute one's own image in the nearest reflective surface. Wrongful discarding of this cape is a capital offence.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The A/RL-66 ROCKET TURRET is a valuable tool for the Helldivers as it provides autonomous anti tank capability. The Turret fires salvos of rockets and tries to asses the damage before firing again to save ammunition. Take care not to stand behind the turret due to the exhaust produced when it fires.
A paint job for use in forest environments.
The Atlas Automatic Cannon's ammunition storage has been improved. It now fires one more salvo.
The unblinking eye represents ceaseless vigilance against bugs and benevolent surveillance of all Helldivers.
Expands the storage capacity for excess heat to increase the fire duration. This increases the fire duration from 25 to 35 seconds.
The lightning can now split 3 more times between targets so it will increase the amount of possible targets from 3 to 6.
After extensive testing in Patriotic Rehabilitation Centres, this design was proved most terrifying to dissent-afflicted individuals.
The LAV can take more damage before it is destroyed.

A single solid lead projectile made to expand when it hits its target. Great for longer ranges and delivers a massive impact on whatever it hits. It's a soft projectile that has trouble with anything harder than medium armour, but it can still do damage to some heavier targets.
Creates a large, thick smoke screen to block targets' line of sight.
Designed by fashion legend RH Gant, the pattern seen on this cape also appears on domestic dresses and gun-warmers.
Armour-piercing explosive rounds, effective against light vehicle armour.
The symbol on this cape represents the pillars of freedom: duty, obedience, and loyalty.
This modest cape has been worn by those guarding the Chamber of Unanimous Decision since time immemorial.
Durable, waterproof, and thermally-lined, surplus units of this cape are favoured by domestic campers, to make tents.
Stuns enemies performing melee attacks. Must recharge for <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>.
A powerful automated turret, effective against armoured targets. The turret will primarily aim at larger enemies.
Developed by the Ministry of Science while investigating the phenomenon known as The Gloom, this armour is non-permeable and squeak resistant.
The number of times the Autocannon Sentry can be called down during a missions is increased from 3 to 4 times.
The Missile needs 1 second less to lock onto the target.
Lethal toxins are stored within the projectile which shatter on impact
Features a utility belt with pockets that can be filled with any number of things, such as pocket knives, mementos from home, and interesting rocks.

For precision-focused Helldivers. 
Specialises in Eagle air support, mobility and long-range warfare.
A backpack which can be wielded as a one-handed ballistic shield, protecting against small arms fire.
This patriotic armour comes recommended by the Ministry of Expansion, empowering the wearer to re-seize from our enemies any territory that any human has laid claim to, at any point in time.
The three stripes on the pauldrons stand for the three principles of Super Earth: Liberty, Democracy, and Prosperity.
It is well-documented that soldiers raised on harsh planets have an advantage when fighting in similar environments; this insight is foundational to the Democratic Youth Scouts Exchange Program.

This cape recalls the popular folk tale of the "Freedomslingers": re-educated dissidents, seeking redemption on the Federation's Borderline, hunting dangerous thought-traitors in exchange for ballot bounties.
Featuring an ancient sun symbol and a distressed look, this cape reminds us that the light of Liberty is everlasting, and will keep shining even when we ourselves have become tattered and frayed.
The Mine deployer can now be deployed faster from the Destroyer. Spawn time reduced from 5 to 3 seconds.
The memory of the Martian training grounds will endure, even after all the Helldivers who trained there have passed, some day in the far future.
Named for Helldiver Jack Boote, who shut down 908 illegal broadcasts before retiring with honours.

As documented in the bestselling graphic novel "The Breach," the final mission of the 361st "Freedom's Flame" saw the storied unit deploy straight into the heart of a Supervolcano, sacrificing themselves to trigger an eruption and wipe out a massive Terminid swarm.
A modified Breaker shotgun firing incendiary projectiles. Generates heat during use, so limited to burst fire.
A modified Liberator firing concussive rounds which do less damage but stagger enemies.
The Crew has prepacked crates based on your team's loadout, further hastening the resupply of ammunition. Cooldown is reduced by 60 Seconds.

The AIRBURST STRIKE is a single larger specialised projectile fired from the Helldiver Destroyer's 408mm cannons. The shot is programmed to explode above the ground and separate into multiple flechettes, each with their own explosive warhead. Extremely effective against unarmoured infantry, the fact that it's a single round allows for fairly frequent firing.
A magazine with a very high capacity at the cost of being bulky and heavy.
A single-use weapon that fires a missile containing napalm cluster bombs that release upon impact.
The Sniper Rifle is equipped with light weight magazines, making it possible to carry more during a mission.
This is essentially like firing small hand grenades at a target.
Rifle round with added micro-propellant that increases ballistics at the cost of velocity.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A rack of semi-guided 100-kg bombs, intended to be dropped on a area target in a high speed flyby. The bomb pattern produces a carpet of explosions killing most infantry, but has a harder time affecting armoured targets unless they are directly hit by one of the bombs. A great option for creating pause in an enemy advance or taking out larger concentrations of infantry.
The number of times the Gatling Sentry can be called down during a missions is increased from 3 to 4 times.
The Railgun's rounds have an improved lightweight casing that allows the Helldiver to carry more during a mission.
Upgrades to the target acquisition allows for more rounds on target. Each salvo fires two shots.
Users are advised not to scratch at the lacquer, as the Red 20,000 pigment that gives this armour its signature sheen may be correlated with rapid DNA unspooling.
An advanced angled foregrip to improve weapon stability.
A shorter magazine with lower capacity, making it lighter and easier to handle.
The number of times the Heavy Machine gun emplacement can be called in is increased from 3 to 4 times.

(NOT IMPLEMENTED) The JAR rifle fires a very heavy round with a small jet-propulsion charge at the end of it, accelerating the shot and extending its range greatly.

The weapon is very accurate but the large rounds are complicated and can not be fired too rapidly due to disturbing other projectiles with their backwash. Great at killing large tough things like alien crustaceans.
Inside the collar is embroidered: "Wherever I may plant my shield, know that I will never yield," and "machine washable".

An illumination flare is fired from your ship in orbit to light up the battlefield. It will start burning and give roughly 100 seconds of magnesium fuelled light. Highly recommended on night missions.
A Hellpod containing a Super Solid State Drive, the peak of secure data storage. Used by Helldivers for everything from transfer of patriotic data to the sabotage of enemy mainframes.
The muted colours and relaxed, high-mobility fit make this a favourite among long-distance snipers and hide-and-seek champions alike.

The standard shotgun ammunition type. Fires a swarm of lead balls that spread over distance. Great for close combat and extremely effective against lightly armoured targets. The spread can be modified by a choke (muzzle attachment) to be tighter or spread differently over longer distances. Virtually useless against armour.
This armour uses repurposed metal from verified sources, such as vending machine packaging and Automaton scrap, making it a sustainable choice for the environmentally conscious Helldiver.
The LAV can carry more magazines for the LMG mounts.
An automated flamethrower turret. Warning: fuel canister prone to explosion when ruptured.
Made famous by the "Truth Enforcers: Enforcers of Truth" mystery novels, this armour calls to mind those paragons of patriotism who protect us from treasonous lies.
Markers placed on the map will generate radar scans every <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>.
Heavy Projectile with better damage and ballistics, the downside is the worse accuracy.
A very powerful but difficult-to-wield machine gun with intense recoil.
A single-use weapon specialised for damaging vehicle armour targets. Discarded after every use.
Supplies are always on standby and are immediately dispatched from the ship when called in.
The cape's shredded hem presages the unrelenting savagery its wielder will visit upon the nemeses of Freedom.
The number of times the Mortar Sentry can be called down during a missions is increased from 3 to 4 times.
A variation on the reflex sight.
The crest on this armour's shoulder shows friendlies that safety is near, and foes that they have reached the end of the road.
A projectile which releases a cloud of caustic gas, blinding and slowing most enemies.
A camo paint job for use in desert environments.
The CW-22 Kodiak armour was thoroughly pressure-tested by patriotic volunteers, as part of the "Test Subjects for Super-Earth" Citizen Advancement Program.
You can choose between HE and HEAT settings with the weapon function.
Each Hellpod is loaded with 4 weapons instead of 2.
The pattern used for this armour is the result of the Winter Camouflage Improvement Effort, which considered 136 entrants before determining the colour white would best blend in with snow.
The HE rounds have a larger explosion radius and the HEAT rounds have a flatter armour-piercing value so it will bounce less often.
With its rustic charm and huntsmanlike detailing, this armour evokes those heroic expansionists who braved the alien wilds and ushered in our current age of bio-uniformity.
By reminding Chemical Agents of proper distancing rules, this extraordinary innovation in cape design ensures that they never cause another unfortunate outbreak of Carcino-Plague.
The signature orange pauldron allows easy battlefield detection of the bearer, alive or dead, on ash-strewn battlefields.
The Arc Throwers arc will do more damage.
A reliable assault rifle with an antique iron sight, firing incendiary ammunition.
"The ground is just another obstacle that hasn't yet been cleared." - SGM Janet Jones, Excavation Corps Founder.
The patented fabric absorbs visible, infrared, and ultraviolet radiation, to prevent detection by all known species.

For technology-focused Helldivers. 
Specialised in utilising offensive and defensive high-tech gadgetry in warfare.
The Sniper Rifle is equipped with larger magazines that can carry more rounds.
This armour, together with its friendly-faced helmet, is instantly recognisable from the beloved children's show 'Jen Shriver the Science Diver'.
A humane, autonomous drone equipped with a modified Arc Thrower. Capable of projecting arcs of lightning through multiple targets. Does not need to recharge between shots.
The SEAF standard assault rifle, balancing power, fire rate, and weight for a reliable weapon against smaller targets.
Gifted to Helldivers whose civilian lives were distinguished by exemplary citizenship, patriotism, and service to the Federation.
A vastly improved afterburner is installed giving the EAGLE a faster pull out time and shortening the time before it is ready to attack again.
A thermite grenade designed to adhere to surfaces before burning at 2000°C. Capable of burning through some armour.
A backpack-mounted Hellbomb that can be armed by the wearer or an ally, starting a countdown. Users are recommended to remove the backpack before the countdown reaches zero.
Equipped with the latest computational systems, subsystems, and supersystems, this armour is worth the equivalent of a small Megacity.
Adds a weapon function that increases or decreases damage, but which also increases or decreases heat build-up.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The orbital stun is a special shot fired from the Helldiver Destroyers 408mm cannons containing multiple devices that with sound, light, and electromagnetic pulses disorient and disables a wide variety of targets temporarily. While the Helldivers are trained to withstand this effect it can still severely lower your combat efficiency should you be hit, though that is preferable to death.
The Orbital Gatling Cannon has been equipped with a splurge friendly drum, increasing the fire time from 4.5 to 9 seconds
A barrage of bombs creating a non-targeted carpet of explosions.

The base module for all Helldivers.
Gives the Helldiver a few basic tools before choosing other ship modules.
Increases the fire rate of the weapon.
Prevents <c=#COLOR>all damage from bleeding</c> if chest haemorrhages.
A manned gun emplacement offering superior firepower against lightly armoured targets. Slow to turn, so place it wisely.
Fires a ballistic dart at near-supersonic speeds, allowing the user to stim allies from a distance. Might sting.
The standard heatsink for laser rifles.

(NOT YET IMPLEMENTED) The 'DEFENDER' uses a proprietary 12.5mm-long pistol-style cartridge that packs one hell of a punch.

The on-top magazine holds 30 rounds, and a special recoil system coupled with the low rate of fire makes this an extremely stable gun for full-auto fire.
Incendiary capsules that contain E-710 and a primer, sets targets on fire.
A medium armoured transport vehicle accomodating a crew of 4. A driver, a gunner for the 40mm autocannon, and 2 seats in the transport compartment armed with STALWART LMGs.
Featuring patented reverse-seam technology, to reduce the likelihood of bodily fluids entering the armour's interior.
Fires a spray of steel spikes that spread over distance.

A single fin-stabilised round packed to the brim with high-explosive compound. Essentially like firing small hand grenades but with very little shrapnel. Good against light and medium armoured enemies.
Fires a spray of lead balls that spread over distance.
The standard shotgun ammunition type. Great for close combat and extremely effective against lightly armoured targets. Virtually useless against armour.
Wearer makes <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> less noise when moving.
Improved high speed servos allow for the turret to rotate significantly faster.
Made famous by the SEAF commander of the same name, this seal reminds us that only perfect Unity can ensure perfect Freedom.
A linear artillery barrage which moves at intervals, driving the enemy out from cover while allowing an advance.
All Hail the Helldivers, whose resplendent honour makes Tyrants tremble.
The omission of upper-limb coverings allows for optimised freedom of movement, perspiration, and communication of upper body strength to squadmates.
All Hail the Helldivers, who bring untold abundance to Super Earth's citizens.
A subdued cape, for those who need no recognition—save that of their enemies, as their executioner.

Often showcased in the "Obedient Democracy Support Troopers" cartoon, this assault rifle comes with a convenient ammo counter and compass.
Produced by Martian Armoury.
The bombs are filled with more napalm at higher pressures, resulting in larger areas covered in fire.
This grenade delivery drone follows the user until it detects an enemy nearby, then flies toward it and explodes on impact. Has a limited battery life.
Based on a SEAF Signaller's Cape, which was intended to enable easy location of fallen heroes by aerial recovery crews.
The explosive compound is switched out for a more powerful one, resulting in more damage.
Armour-piercing bullet with improved penetration capabilities.
A symbol of fierce commitment to Liberty and Democracy, this cape celebrates the Helldivers who have held true to Super Earth values through rain or shine.
Single high velocity sabot that does massive damage and has high armour piercing capability.
A Hellpod containing four supply packs, to replenish personal ammunition and stims in the field.
A melee weapon tipped with electrified prongs that temporarily stun targets. Can be wielded one-handed.
A sight with thin features to maximize visibility of the target.
The featherlight construction belies the heavy burden this cape entails—to live the Creed of the True Citizen.
Armour Piercing Tipped Ammunition that does less damage to unarmoured targets.
The heavy rubber tunic and reflective limb guards, originally designed to save citizens from burning buildings, now enable the liberal application of the cleansing fires of Justice.
A modified Breaker shotgun firing birdshot, small pellets which saturate an area to clear up smaller targets.
A shovel that can be used as a melee weapon or, more conventionally, to dig holes in the ground.
The number of times the Energy shield emplacement can be called in is increased from 3 to 4 times.
Modelled after the myriad Statues of Judicious Liberty, who keep a watchful eye on checkout lines, schoolyards, perpetual rehabilitation communities, and public confession theatres.
The Light Machinegun is equipped with a larger magazine, with its capacity increased from 75 to 150 rounds.
When wearers stand shoulder to shoulder, this cape shows them as they truly are: an unbreakable defence, keeping Freedom safe behind an impregnable wall.
The turret is equipped with a drum magazine, significantly improving ammunition capacity.
The Rail Cannon target lock-on time is decreased by 1 second.
Allows the swift completion of Liberty's administrative tasks in an invigorating atmosphere.
Granted to the Truth Enforcers' Informant of the Month, this tasteful cape conjures images of dissident blood on asphalt.
A throwable device engineered to bounce when hitting the ground, releasing bursts of electricity on each impact. Warning: may bounce unpredictably.
Plasma cored warhead that detonates with super heated gas.
Heavily insulated from animal bites, enemy fire, and the histrionic diatribes of anarchists.
The backpack is loaded with 5 more magazines.
A shotgun used in colonies to hunt and protect from threats.
The thumper is equipped with a piston, used for sending out strong vibrations into the ground, which disrupt nearby bug nests.
A prolonged barrage, wreaking extended destruction over a large area. Communication with teammates is advised.
The missile has a larger explosion radius.
A upgraded shotgun ammunition type. Great for close combat and extremely effective against lightly armoured targets. Virtually useless against armour.
An anti-tank homing missile which must lock onto its target before launch. Effective against large and armoured enemies.
Higher quality servos makes the sentry capable of rotation and elevation at the same time. Also slightly improves the speed at which it turns.
A barrage of smoke grenades, creating a thick smoke screen to block enemies' line of sight.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The 'Sickle' was developed as a response to the first insurrection on Marre IV where the Deathtrooper unit of the Helldivers quickly became starved for ammunition and had to resort to melee combat against the renegade colonists.
A silo that fits one single, powerful missile. Comes with a handheld targeting remote.
Single slug that does massive damage.
A laser rifle firing a continuous beam. Does not need reloading, but if it overheats a new heat sink must be fitted.
Provides <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> resistance to gas damage and effects.
The wheels can take more damage before they are destroyed.
The crew has prepared ammunition for your equipment ahead of time and stand ready to fill a new pod. Cooldown is reduced by 30 seconds.
Plasma cored warhead that detonates with super heated gas.

Inspired by the trailblazing agents of the Super Earth Terraforming Company. These rugged adventurers surveyed hostile new planets during the post-GW1 Great Expansion era, preparing the untamed frontier for rapid and efficient assimilation.
The standard scope for most weapons, provides a good and accurate scope picture.
With this cape we honour the bio-warfare pioneers of Division Zero, conscripted from quarantine zones and hospices to spread their Carcino-Plague on the battlefield.

NOT IMPLEMENTED Used as the Super Earth Armed Forces standard answer to armoured opposition, the recoilless rifle offers great anti armour capabilities in a very portable package. The weapon system requires support ammunition carried in a separate backpack and is best operated as a two man team with the loader carrying ammunition. The weapon can be reloaded by the weapon operator in a pinch should he have ammunition available.
Improved gunpowder propels the projectile at higher velocity reducing the travel time and increasing damage.
Those who serve Liberty from the shadows often elect to stay anonymous, moving like traceless spectres through the night. May they watch over us always.
A plasma rifle that fires bolts of superheated gas, which can be charged by holding down the trigger. Charging up a shot fully makes the bolt explode on impact.
Fires a rocket that detonates within proximity of a target, and deploys a cluster of explosive bomblets.
Armour piercing bullet with improved penetration capabilities.
A silenced assault rifle with a built-in suppressor, which won't alert distant targets to the user's position.
Expanding projectile that does massive damage against unarmoured targets.
The gas-operated, semiautomatic P-113 chambers the 14mm "Rapid Deliberation," the largest centrefire cartridge of any magazine-fed pistol.
Contains a grain of sand from Super Earth — so its bearers carry a small piece of Liberty with them, wherever they go.
Encloses the wearer in a spherical shield which blocks high-speed projectiles.
Each round is filled with more explosive mass contributing to a slightly larger explosion.
A basic iron sight for Helldivers who want to relive the glorious struggles of their ancestors.
The magazines are loaded with a 8mm APT bullet every third round. This makes it more effective against heavy infantry units.
A triple-barrelled, break-action, sawed-off shotgun. Switch firing modes to fire all three barrels at once.
Adjusted tension on the breech lock results in faster projectile speed, at the cost of increased recoil.
A half-constricted muzzle that forces the shotgun pellets together into a somewhat tighter group.
The crew has been drilled to reload the cannon faster, reducing the time between uses. Cooldown is lowered by 15 seconds.
The standard 20mm AP-E round is an armour piercing projectile with a small amount of explosive mass, designed to breach through lighter armour and then explode inside.
Modelled after the Statue of Mournful Liberty, who weeps over the existence of tyranny, this armour is worn by those who would give their lives to dry her tears.
Shell contains three heavy projectiles that cause massive damage to unarmoured targets.
A lightweight melee weapon that temporarily stuns enemies.
The Commando is equipped with missiles that have higher Armour Penetration.
A Hellpod containing four supply packs, to replenish personal ammunition and stims in the field.
Spattered gore marks those heroes who braved the harrowing first days of the war for Managed Democracy.
Air brakes and smart acceleration protocols allow for longer time with nose on target. Extends the fire time and area coverage for each run with 30%.

Since ancient times, the yellow line has symbolised an uncrossable boundary. To don this cape is to draw that line between tyranny and liberty, between alien monstrosities and Super Earth property, and never yield the right of way.
The shield power is boosted significantly, resulting in the shield being able to take double the amount of punishment before failing.
The Walking Barrage will fire two more salvoes.
All but ensures ascension to the immortal ranks of those enshrined in the Super Earth Digital Archive of Valorous Acts.
The set's classic advertising campaign "Have you tried a grenade?" has remained unchanged for over 70 years.
0.05% of profits are donated to Superstone National Park, as part of the Ministry of Unity's "Greener Galaxy" campaign.
Though originally intended solely for ceremonial use, its inspirational energy proved equally useful on the battlefield.
A speargun firing heavy-duty projectiles. These projectiles release a cloud of gas on impact, and must be carefully loaded one at a time.
Woven in honour of our loyal Helldivers, whose commitment to Democracy, through rain or shine, is an inspiration to all.
A constricted muzzle that forces the shotgun pellets together into a tighter group.
A heatsink with thinner cooling elements, improving cooling rate.
A fully-automatic pistol with an extremely high fire rate, allowing for efficient crowd control.
Round with high armour-piercing capability due to the inner core forged out of Super Uranium. Added effect is radiation damage.
A tube red dot sight with 2x magnification, good for hitting small targets consistently over medium range.
As the electric arc generates a strong magnetic field, wearers should avoid use while in vicinity of stapled paperwork.
Debuted during the New Mombasa Armour Show, this sleek ensemble is sure to turn heads and blow minds.
Let all who see this cape be struck still with Freedom's beauty, or struck dead with Liberty's bullets.
Punisher shotgun variant modifier with burst fire of incendiary round and a large drum magazine.
Launches a prolonged barrage of napalm shells over a wide area, setting a swath of land ablaze in mere moments.
A larger heatsink that can store more heat.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The 'REDEEMER' is a fully automatic pistol with an extremely high rate of fire. The pistol gets very hard to control when firing full auto and is recommended for short range use only.

The burst mass of the pistol is unparalleled by other sidearms and pointing it at a target and unloading the entire magazine will put down most light to medium targets.
The machine gun sentry's magazine capacity is increased from 125 to 200 rounds.
This armour is based on the antique uniforms of the 'Super Earth Legion', a less patriotic precursor to the Helldivers.
This cape reminds us that even faced with the abyssal darkness of space, nothing can stand against our human ingenuity, our powers of collaboration, or our sheer overwhelming numbers.
A camo paint job for use in arctic environments.
Some say that a mere glimpse of this cape, fluttering majestically in the breeze, is enough to spur a squad to victory.
A turret firing powerful shells in a high arc. Effective at long ranges, and able to strike at targets behind cover.
Expanded bomb racks allows for more bombs in each run, cutting a bigger swath out of the enemies' numbers.
The Gatling mount magazine can carry more rounds.

A variation of the Buckshot round but with small steel spikes instead of lead balls. Does less damage but handles armour better and maintains more destructive capabilities over longer range. The spread can be modified by a choke (muzzle attachment) to be tighter or spread differently over longer distances.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The best minds of Super Earth have over the years realised that rotary weapon systems shoot, a lot. They have since conceived of an orbital version of the rotary weapons commonly mounted on Helldiver vehicles and Hellpod stratagems.
A prism which creates a more focused beam that has better armour piercing at the best angle and worse armour piercing in all other angles.
Emblazoned with the red, white, and green of the 676th Democracy Regiment, who made their final stand on the slopes of Justice Hill.
Expanding projectile that does massive damage against unarmoured targets.
A thinner bomb casing allows for more explosives in each bomb. Increases explosion radius.
An improved mix of flash fragments, senor disrupting drugs and chaff material extends the duration of the Static Field Conductors by 5 seconds.

A one-handed device that deploys a wide energy barrier in front of the user. The barrier is semipermeable and blocks high-speed projectiles from the outside only, leaving the user free to shoot through it.
Due to the enhanced strength caused by this armour, caution is advised when using door handles or embracing colleagues.
A grenade that releases a cloud of toxic gas, effective at temporarily blinding and slowing both organic and inorganic enemies.
A version of the standard drum but with better ergonomics.
A grenade launcher effective against armoured infantry. Not intended for use against vehicle armour or fortified buildings.
This armour set first appeared in the music video for the summer anthem 'Our Love is Like Liberty (Indestructible)'.
The missile is deployed faster from the silo, reducing the deploy time from 3 to 0.5 seconds.
A single precision shot from the Destroyer's 'ATLAS' cannon.
Ammo capacity in each turret increases from 400 to 600 rounds.
Reduces range at which enemies can detect the wearer by <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The 'BREAKER' is a fully automatic low-recoil 12g shotgun. Its close-combat capabilities are terrifying and it can use a wide range of specialised ammunition, making it a very effective weapon on mid-range and crowd suppression.

Produced by Browfors Arms, the shotgun is used in the SEAF as a room clearing weapon and in rare cases as fire support.
Temporarily stuns all targets within the effective radius.
Contains many small pockets, allowing the user to evenly distribute the weight of ammunition, samples, and cool rocks.
Woven in honour of our loyal citizens, who by raising their voices have supported the war effort more than they can ever know.
A compact version of the Liberator designed for increased viability in close quarters. Has an increased fire rate at the cost of higher spread.
Aspect-seeking air-to-air missiles, to eliminate most flying targets in the vicinity.
The standard magazine for 15mm JAR rounds.
Expanded bomb racks allows for more bombs to be dropped each run, resulting in a longer line of napalm.
A heavily-armoured walking exosuit equipped with dual autocannons.
Reduces the size of the muzzle flash by dispersing the burning propellant when firing the weapon.
Legend tells of the unnamed Helldiver, wandering the edges of Super Earth's reach, delivering Democracy and levelling lawlessness wherever the tumbleweeds lead. Wear this, and keep the legend alive.
A drill capable of piercing the tough walls of Terminid hives, and deploying a nuclear charge to collapse all tunnels.
A plasma rifle, firing a bolt of superheated gas which explodes on impact. Avoid standing in proximity to the blast.
Multiple low damage pellets for unarmoured targets.
Redirects propellant gases to compensate for muzzle climb when firing the weapon.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The Expendable Anti-Tank is a one shot support weapon specialised at taking out armoured targets. Though you can carry only one, they are cheap and easy to deploy and can serve as a great on demand anti-armour weapon should you encounter unexpected enemy armour.
A high-velocity railcannon round fired at the largest target in close proximity to the beacon. Targeting is automatic.
The heavy machine gun now has a smaller recoil with sustained fire. Sadly, we could not improve the recoil for the first few shots.
A barrage of rocket pods, which the Eagle pilot will release on the largest target near the stratagem beacon.
A improved targeting system allows the Static Field Conductors to be deployed at the target area 2 seconds faster.
Round with high armour-piercing capability due to the inner core forged out of Super Uranium. Added effect is radiation damage.
A recoilless rifle effective against vehicle armour. Includes support backpack required for reloading.
Improved guidance programming and propulsion boosters makes them hit with even more consistency.
Increases reload speed of primary weapons by <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>.
Round that on impact explodes into shrapnel.
This ceremonial rifle is modelled after antique relics from pre-Democratic times. It is traditionally gifted to every citizen upon turning 16 to encourage service.
A strafing run of the battlefield to clear small targets, delivered almost instantly.
On impact the projectile melts the armour of the target.
When children have trouble sleeping, tucking them in under this cape reminds them that they are never alone, for Liberty's unseen defenders are always watching over them.
The Hellpod is loaded with two machineguns so you can spread the joy or maybe have a spare when you do not have time to reload.
After colonists of Hellmire recovered a lost shipment of this armour, the local pastime of fence-smashing was born.
The Walking Barrage will fire 2 more bombs per salvo.
The turret interprets Helldivers' commands, and no longer requires line of sight to marked targets.
Deploys a defensive anti-personnel minefield to halt enemy advance.
A plasma igniter that reduces the spread of the plasma bolt.
Increases initial inventory and holding capacity of stims by <c=#COLOR>#SIGN#BONUS</c>.
An experimental weapon which prioritises armour penetration. Must be charged between shots - so choose targets carefully.
The Combat Walker's fuel capacity is increased by 50%.
Gives better general recoil and less noise at the cost of ergonomics.
A powerful plasma weapon that fires one blast at a time, each blast exploding on impact. Must be charged to fire. Warning: do not overcharge.
One of the earliest to be mass-produced, this cape has been the final sight of untold numbers of Freedom's foes.
The number of times the Anti-Personnel Mine Deployer emplacement can be called in is increased from 3 to 4 times.
Body type has no impact on gameplay
This bolt-action rifle fires jet-assisted shells that explode shrapnel in all directions upon impact. Not recommended for close-quarters use.
Each purchase of this cape comes with a complimentary will and testament amendment form, which guarantees the soon-to-be-deceased a prominent spot on the Wall of Martyrs.
Every other projectile have been replaced with an armour-piercing round to make it more efficient against armoured infantry units.
A one-handed ceremonial sword suitable for use in parades, sabrage, and combat.
The number of times the Defence wall can be called in is increased from 5 to 6 times.
Heavy Projectile with better damage and ballistics, the downside is the worse accuracy.
The AAPF rounds are designed for surface to air combat against lightly armoured fliers.

Heavily layered to protect against ocular blistering, subdermal liquification, and gastrointestinal shattering, this armour is a testament to the power of iterative improvements based on user feedback.
The installation of an auto-loader allows the crew to fill a reloadable magazine, reducing the time between uses. Cooldown is lowered by 30 seconds.
Scatters powerful anti-tank mines that deal heavy, armour-penetrating damage. Minefield is less densely packed relative to smaller mines.
A magazine that contains more rounds at the cost of number of magazines. It allows the Helldiver to carry more overall ammo and reload less often.
Armour Piercing Tipped Ammunition that does less damage to unarmoured targets.
A projected laser, that is aligned with the barrel of the weapon, which assists the user with landing their shots.

[Not implemented] The E/DEF-10 COVER WALL was developed to grant Helldivers cover where none was naturally occurring. The cover deploys a sturdy wall complete with a floor covering, providing ideal cover. The cover is resistant to most small arms fire, but anti-tank weapons will have no issues destroying it.
For warriors who are so strong and confident that they don't need any reassurance whatsoever.
Humanity's intellect shines brighter than all other, piercing even the treacherous darkness that spawned the Automatons' pseudo-sentience; the darkness known as computer science.
The Hellbomb is a tactical nuke powerful enough to destroy any perceivable target in its blast zone. For safety and budgetary reasons, it has to be armed manually once deployed.
The autocannons magazines capacity is increased from 150 rounds to 200 rounds each.
Created to honour the great Freedom Chant of 14/2, in which over 10,000 loyal citizens united as one to express their undying respect for Freedom.
The Supply Backpack can now carry 6 boxes of ammunition.
Special Assassin round developed to combat Automaton Hulks.
The Sniper Rifle is equipped with improved anti-material rounds that inflict more damage.
Improved gunpowder propels the projectile at higher velocity reducing the travel time and increasing damage.
A larger napalm canister allowing for more fire and destruction before you have to reload. Increases capacity by approximately 45%.
The default paint job for this weapon.
Marks the most obedient of the obedient, those who will strike headlong at the veins of Tyranny and administer the sweet antidote of Freedom.
The weapon needs 0.5 seconds less time to lock on target.
A camo paint job for use in urban environments.
The Vehicle can store more magazines for the HMG mount.
Several medium damage pellets for unarmoured targets.
A turret firing powerful and precise laser beams. Warning: overloading heat sink may cause adverse effects.
The Atlas Automatic Cannon's ammunition storage has been perfected. It now fires 6 salvoes instead of 4.
Explosive tipped projectile that does high damage against massive unarmoured targets.
A paint job that is one with the darkness.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The E/HMG-23 HEAVY MACHINEGUN is a turret requiring a crew of 1, armed with two highly destructive 12.5mm machineguns. The emplacement is extremely good at handling large amounts of medium armoured enemies. Caution should be used when manning the E/HMG-23 as crew members are exposed to enemy fire while crewing the weapon.
Fires a timed delay round that explodes into shrapnel.
Each magazine carried by the drone now contains more ammunition.
Enables the user to jump higher than 'gravity' and 'safety' would normally allow. Must be charged before use.
Upgraded ammunition feed now allows for more rounds per salvo. Each salvo now fires three rounds.
The missile launcher fires missiles with higher damage.
Based on a colonial surgeon's gown, where surgeries were often interrupted by a need to perform defensive duties.
Adorned with the insignia of the Order of the Venerated Ballot, a Ministry-sanctioned Patriot's Club for citizens who pledge themselves to preserving the sanctity of voting.
Improves weapons handling with less drag on weapon movement.
A large-capacity assault rifle firing humane stun rounds. Reports of lethal incidents have been thoroughly debunked.
The crew is drilled in the process of reloading the air burst round, resulting in a faster turnaround time before being able to shoot again. Cooldown decreased by 15 seconds.
Crests the shoulders of those who deliver the final—and most indispensable—stroke of Justice.
The grenade launcher is equipped with a 40mm Grenades with a programmable charge. The explosive charge can be switch between a stun charge and the regular explosive charge.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A linear artillery barrage fired by the 408mm cannons of the Helldiver Destroyer in low orbit. The barrage continues down a line up to approximately 50 metres, obliterating most things in its way. Extreme caution is advised when using this stratagem in the way of strategic objectives and friendly lines.
The Missiles will hit the target faster and more reliably.

The 'DAGGER' is a pistol based on a scaled down version of the 'SCYTHE'. It fires a continuous beam capable of heating up surfaces to extreme temperatures in seconds.

The beam is focused on extreme distance but can be focused further using different prisms, allowing for greater damage if used correctly. Refocusing the beam reduces the efficiency for the non-focused interval.
Shrapnel charges that detonate when close to moving objects, effective against light, fast-moving targets.
Hyper Velocity Round with a serious kick.
Some soldiers report picking up strange radio interference when wearing this armour near alien artefacts.
An incendiary weapon for close range. Will ignite targets, terrain, and any flammable teammates.
The burnished blood-red plates are forged in righteous fire, like the heroes they were wrought to protect.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The A/MG-11 GATLING SENTRY is a beloved staple of the Helldivers, capable of shredding light targets en masse. Like all automated sentries it can distinguish between friend and foe and will target only enemies, but it has no safety mechanism that will prevent it from firing if a friendly is in the way of its target. It is highly recommended to stay behind the turret, though that might be difficult as it has a 360 degree field of fire.
Woven in honour of our loyal Helldivers, whose heart's blood is the foundation on which Super Earth is built.
The LAV can carry more rounds for the autocannon turret.
With extra initial fuse this rocket travels much faster than its regular counterparts.
A stationary energy shield which provides cover against projectiles. Has a limited lifetime once deployed.
An advanced vertical foregrip to improve the manoeuvrability of the weapon.
The default trigger for rifles. Gives no modifications to weapon.
The yellow is the exact shade of the Ministry of Unity's 'Golden Gate', leading to the Chamber of Unanimous Decision.
Based on the ceremonial pennant flags of early Super Earth, which now adorn the entrance to each Ministry.
An experimental compressed explosive is used instead of the standard, giving a much bigger boom. Explosion radius is increased from 10m to 12m.
This humane device attaches to its target and dispenses repeated electrical pulses, keeping the target in place for humane apprehension and/or termination.
A pistol firing bursts of guided, jet-propelled ammunition. Can be set to non-guided mode at any time, removing the need to lock on to targets.
The Laser Cannon is equipped with one more magazine.
Body type has no impact on gameplay
Part of a long line of experimental armour commonly seen on industrial engineering campuses, in the basements of select science aficionados, and around Super Destroyer Mega Garages.
The explosive compound is switched out for a more powerful one, resulting in more damage.
The Walking Barrage requires less down time. Cooldown is reduced by 15 seconds.
Rifle round with added micro-propellant that increases ballistics at the cost of velocity.
Houses the Eagle Fighter & Pelican Shuttle. Also receives deliveries of materiel, supplies, frozen personnel, and fuel.
A targeting remote, used in combination with the Solo Silo.
The unimpeachable justice of this cape's design is said to blind the enemies of Freedom with its glorious light.
A high-calibre assault rifle with a restrictive magazine size but more stopping power.
The embroidered pattern uses aluminium from Automaton motherboards, granting the once-wretched metals a new and noble purpose.
First deployed in the Helldivers "Diplomatic" Corps, this armour enables effective non-verbal interspecies communication.
Detonates nearby enemies and showers the target in shrapnel.
A simple vertical foregrip to improve the manoeuvrability of the weapon.
A modified Punisher shotgun firing heavy, high-damage slug rounds. Perfect for punching big holes in big targets.
This sigil reaffirms the Helldiver's pledge to protect Managed Democracy, serve Managed Democracy, and uphold Managed Democracy.
This armour is the Super Earth Standard Issue, made from the same titanium alloy as the Destroyer's hull.
A heavier version of the Breaker shotgun, with higher damage at the cost of recoil and manoeuvrability.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The O-X32 is an experimental anti ship laser used for pinpoint strikes against enemy weak points. The laser is so energy dense that it has no issue cutting through the atmosphere of most planets and has found great use as a support weapon against ground targets. The laser generates an extreme amount of heat and the process of cooling the heat exchangers down takes a substantial amount of time.
Installation of high-speed servos significantly increases the turrets max turn speed, making it get the muzzle on target faster.
The Laser Cannon is equipped with a better heatsink and can fire for a longer time before it needs to cool down.
Each gilded detail is polished to perfection by re-educated dissidents, as part of the Lifelong Post-Infraction Atonement Program.
Improved targeting allows for more missiles to be shot at the same time, increasing the firepower of the run.
This cape signifies that its wearer thinks, feels, and acts correctly at all times, and thus bears the responsibility to educate and re-educate their fellow citizen.
Better use of alloys and lighter materials in the construction of the weapon makes it significantly easier to handle. Improves Ergonomics by 10.
It is said that only the truly Democratic can lift this cape to their shoulders.
A pistol front-loaded with a single, powerful explosive. The weight of the projectile limits the weapon's range.
Redirects propellant gases to reduce recoil when firing the weapon.
Offers its user brief fixed-height flight, stable enough for pinpoint marksmanship.
Shell contains three heavy projectiles that cause massive damage to unarmoured targets.
A paint job for use in urban environments.
An angled foregrip to improve weapon stability.
A high explosive grenade which damages lightly armoured targets. Creates high damage over a small area when detonated.
Several medium damage pellets for unarmoured targets.
A 'compliance weapon' to modify enemy behaviour. Creates a thick smoke screen to block targets' line of sight.
This aim-stabilising armour found surprising secondary market success among alien birdwatching enthusiasts.
Multiple low damage pellets for unarmoured targets.
An antipersonnel fragmentation grenade. Creates damage over a large area when detonated.
Incendiary capsules that contain E-710 and a primer, sets targets on fire.
A modified Diligence rifle offering increased damage at the cost of some manoeuvrability. Fires a single bullet at a time.
<c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> chance to not die when taking lethal damage.
Improved servos for the aiming of the laser allows for it to move faster, making it more effective at targeting.
A flattened muzzle that forces the shotgun pellets into a thin horizontal line.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A pod of 110mm DRAGON rockets used to strike at armoured targets. Your Eagle pilot will try to pick the best target available based on proximity to your beacon and armour level. The rockets have no guidance and will not always hit the target but this is usually compensated by firing a substantial amount of rockets. The amount of rockets means there might be significant collateral damage in proximity to the target.
Supply boxes containing ammunition, with a backpack that allows the user to distribute boxes to fellow Helldivers.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A blanket artillery barrage fired by the 408mm cannons of the Helldiver Destroyer in low orbit. The barrage carries on for a significant amount of time and will obliterate most things in the targeted area. Extreme caution is advised when using this stratagem near strategic objectives and friendly lines as it can wander slightly.
Increases the amount of grenades in each belt from 6 to 10 rounds.
A pistol that fires grenades. Must be reloaded between shots.
The Covers mounted Light Machinegun is equipped with a larger magazine, with its capacity increased from 75 to 150 rounds.
An accurate, hard-hitting laser revolver with bespoke break action for heat sink swaps.
Patched and tattered, this banner yet waves from the unbowed shoulders of Freedom's most battle-tested warriors.
Features a patented non-stick coating, which makes scraping viscera off after a long day of battle less taxing.
Should the wearer of this cape perish at the hands of Freedom's enemies, it is customary to pass the cape on to their bravest child during the funeral, inspiring the next generation to take up arms.
A Seismic Probe fitted into a Hellpod. Is preprogrammed so that only the simplest calibration and execution sequence is needed once deployed to the surface.
Space is cleared for an auto loader on the middle barrel of each turret, allowing for an additional round per turret to be fired in each salvo.
Creates a far-reaching incendiary blast ideal for crowd control against smaller enemies of Freedom. Equipped with a programmable timer for strategic versatility.
This shotgun blasts a wide burst of high-voltage electricity that arcs between all units—enemy or otherwise—within range.
The distinctive red, white, and green of the Intergalactic Medical Corps signal to all Helldivers that help is at hand.
Improved gunpowder propels the projectile at higher velocity reducing the travel time and increasing damage.
The number of times the Tesla Tower can be called in is increased from 3 to 4 times.
The number of times the Jump pack can be called down during a mission is increased from 1 to 2 times.
Tests and implements the most advanced stratagem technology that funding has been allocated for.
Call in an emergency beacon to show other Helldivers that you need assistance.
Increases ammo capacity of all weapons by <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>. Does not affect weapon backpacks.
This traditional armour has remained unchanged since time immemorial. Now with self-heated padding.
Originally worn by lunar terraformers, this suit can withstand rapid changes in pressure, heat, and personal velocity.
Popularised by actor Chip Messiter, who wore this in the action-rom-com-musical "Lost My Heart to a Man in a Helmet."

A pistol with a built-in laser sight, suppressor, and flashlight.
Produced by Martian Armoury.
A camo paint job for use in forest environments.
The Shield is now twice as durable.
A repurposed firework that showers its immediate surrounding area in sparks before exploding. As delightful as it is incendiary.
Increases initial inventory and holding capacity of throwables by <c=#COLOR>#SIGN#BONUS</c>.
A upgraded version of the shotgun ammunition type with more damage.
Few pellets for lightly armoured targets.
On impact the projectile melts the armour of the target.
Projects an arc of lightning at close range. Charges up to project bolts, and may discharge through multiple targets.
Packed full of high performance gunpowder this round packs a serious punch as well as kick.
The number of times the Defence wall can be called in is increased from 6 to 8 times.
An armour often worn by frontline surgeons, who are skilled at both putting bodies back together and taking them apart.
Gives wearer a <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> chance to avoid grievous limb injury.
Fires a timed delay round that explodes into shrapnel.
Packed full of high performance gunpowder this round packs a serious punch as well as kick.
The number of times the Rocket Sentry can be called down during a missions is increased from 3 to 4 times.
An autonomous drone equipped with a Liberator assault rifle, providing 360° cover. Returns to backpack to rearm.
Equip stratagems to be able to drop into a mission!
Bearers of this cape take upon a sacred duty: that of delivering righteous retribution to every last deserving being.
Delivers silent justice to Freedom's enemies.
Disintegrating expanding projectile with massive damage, poor ballistics and accuracy. Causes chock in enemies hit by the round.
The crew has been drilled to reload the cannon faster, reducing the time between uses. Cooldown lowered by 20 seconds.
A pump shotgun that fires a burst of incendiary phosphorus pellets, setting targets ablaze.
The Tesla Tower can be active for longer. Increased from 3 to 4 minutes.
Research suggests that Helldivers wearing this cape are seen as 17% more patriotic.
Those taken under the wings of the Law can rest easy knowing that their transgressions will soon be laid bare, their harms amended, and their citizenship safely sequestered.
Made famous by the Ministry of Intelligence's hide-and-seek-and-destroy champion of '52, this armour has been improved by removing excess shoulder protection.
Completely sheathed in 14-cm silica fibre foam, except for a thin tube to the ear canal to enable hearing the satisfying screeches of Freedom's enemies as they burn.
Fires a spray of lead pellets that spread over distance.

A versatile missile launcher loaded with seven lock-on homing missiles. These can either be fired from the launcher directly or as an airburst. Includes support backpack required for reloading.
Produced by Stål Arms.
This multi-layered protective armour keeps rough sand, spores, and other course granules from irritating the skin.
Wearers of this stealthy armour are seldom seen by their targets—or squadmates. No refunds if misplaced.
Explosive tipped projectile that does high damage against massive unarmoured targets.
Pick up and use <c=FFFFE900>EXPENDABLE ANTI-TANK</c> against <c=FFFFE900>ARMOURED ENEMIES</c>.

Many ships that attempt to enter Pathfinder space are either never heard from again or end up somewhere else entirely. Surprisingly, this fact hasn't discouraged people from travelling to the system. Instead, it's given rise to a whole new sport known as slip-racing. Ships line up at the edge of the Pathfinder wormhole and shoot through in unison. Whoever winds up furthest from the starting point wins!

Note: in order to be eligible for a Pathfinder slip-race victory, your ship must be located within 6 years of the start of the race. Ships relocated to beyond the edge of the race's military-grade sensors are considered lost.

The Helldivers, in their Democratic direction of the DSS, displayed undeniable tactical brilliance, demonstrating once again why they are known as the Galaxy's most elite fighting force. Their efforts held the Automaton onslaught long enough to allow emergency evacuation efforts to save many citizens, many of whom aided in the construction of the space station. The Jet Brigade remains a significant threat. Meanwhile, the crisis created by the sudden and shocking outbreak at the Terminid Research Centre is ongoing. The addition of the DSS to Liberty's arsenal, even in its diminished state, could not have come at a better time. Managed Democracy is imperilled; we need every weapon at our disposal.
